headline.main: New Zealand FM Optimistic on Finalising Stalled Gulf Trade Deal This Year
headline.print_headline: New Zealand FM Optimistic on Finalising Stalled Gulf Trade Deal This Year

lead_paragraph: New Zealand is optimistic it will complete its stalled free trade deal with the Gulf states this year as part of efforts to deepen economic ties with the region, Minister of Foreign Affairs Murray McCully said on Monday.
